  "body": "Solidity 0.6.3 [introduced](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/releases/tag/v0.6.3) a `revertStrings` setting that adds reason strings for compiler-generated errors.\r\n\r\n1) Right now the Buidler EVM doesn't work well if this setting is enabled (tests fail, at the very least).\r\n2) These added reasons _might_ be useful for Buidler EVM, although since they aren't documented it's not clear if and which of them could be leveraged for things that aren't handled right now. Of course, to do that item 1) should be fixed.",
